user.name: Teresa Snowball
snippet: Only giving this hospital 1 because google wont allow me to give none. My daughter was admitted for emergency brain surgery after HOSPITAL PILAR SCREWED UP, she was taken by ambulance to Hospital clinic instructed by her TERRIBLE NEUROLOGIST who just performed 2 terrible operations at Hospital Pilar. When we arrive to Clinic they told us that she needed emergency brain surgery so was taken immediately to surgery by what we believed was a surgeon as this is what she told us. Her surgeon from Hospital Pilar did not come once to see her even though he also works at Hospital clinic. After finishing surgery at the early morning, I went home and returned to the hospital by 08.00 am being told that she should be taken home, SHE WAS STILL IN ICU and from ICU she should go home without any advise or help from anyone, even her terrible surgeon from Pilar never gave any advice or the new surgeon from Clinic, which we learnt recently that she was not fully qualified, and the operation she performed was also a complete disaster. The names of all the surgeons will be on my next review. LOOK OUT FOR THE NAMES OF THE SURGEONS. And the next part of the journey for my daughter.

user.name: nuria barron rando
snippet:
Soy paciente del hospital clínic desde los 18 años y me llevan por patologías poco comunes. Des de que estoy con ellos tengo la enfermedad estabilizada. Sigo con ellos y recomiendo muchísimo este hospital a cualquier persona.
Si que es verdad que los servicios de urgencias a veces son un poco caos en el sentido de que en los boxes los pacientes estan separados por cortinas y eso no da mucha intimidad que digamos. Lo único que mejoraría es el sistema de urgencias, por lo demás estoy muy contenta.

I have been a patient at the hospital clinic since I was 18 years old and they take me for rare pathologies. Since I have been with them, my disease has stabilized. I continue with them and highly recommend this hospital to anyone.
It is true that emergency services are sometimes a bit chaotic in the sense that in the boxes the patients are separated by curtains and that does not provide much privacy. The only thing that would improve is the emergency system, otherwise I am very happy.
